post_text:
Employment Opportunities:
Bathroom/Social Distancing Monitors*
Responsible for maintaining a limited number of students in the bathroom at a time, encouraging students to socially distance while in hallways, assisting with arrival (AM) and dismissal (PM) of students.

3 - Morning Monitors 8:00AM-12:00PM
3 - Afternoon Monitors 11:30AM - 3:30PM
Pay rate is $12 per hour.

2 Lunch Aides*
(Supervise students during meals and at recess)

$12.00 PER HOUR
Monday – Friday
10:15am – 1:15pm

*These are temporary positions while in a health crisis

See website to apply: Slheights.org

post_text:
Reposted from @slheightspta We would like thank departing SLH PTA Board Members, Susie Caamano and Kristy Sinkhorn for their years of service.

They held two unique and very important roles for the PTA. Susie volunteered as President for two years and then came back this year to serve as treasurer. Kristy volunteered as Corresponding Secretary for two years.

These two women helped us tremendously with their knowledge, craftiness and creativity. We are so appreciative of all the time they gave the PTA and hard work over the years. 💛💙Thank you so very much 💙💛 - #regrann

post_text: In the words of Martin Luther King, Jr. “Darkness cannot drive out darkness; only light can do that. Hate cannot drive out hate; only love can do that.” As a school community, we are saddened by the events unfolding around us which continue to repeat themselves. We are also witnesses to those who stand for what the right thing is and should be. This is an opportunity for all of us to continue to teach our children and those around us the importance of caring for and loving one another. As such, we are launching a #NoHateInHeights social media campaign for our students and community members to share stories and post age-appropriate artistic expressions. Please use this hashtag to promote inclusion, equality, acceptance, and peace.

post_text:
Adults and children are all experiencing a wide range of emotions at this time. Sensing our 8th graders were feeling a bit wistful recently, a few of their teachers identified a teachable moment! They presented the message that sometimes when things have you down, it helps to do something that makes others happy. And the students ran with the idea!! The 8th graders wanted to share some joy with the SLH community, so they created this virtual Pep Rally for you to enjoy! We hope it brings a smile to your faces! Thanks so much to @mrsWojcik1, @schneidersteam, @miss.langslh, @coachCarew7, @Prestonslh, @mrsprestonslh, @mrkforbes, and @msGambinomusic for their dedication to this project and for inspiring our students to spread some cheer! The 8th graders did a phenomenal job!!

https://drive.google.com/file/d/1c3lSXRH9V2TKgehhjyGbHhGh4OMvRqUg/view?usp=drivesdk

Reposted from @slheightspta 🌟THE GREAT JERSEY SHORE TAKE-OUT PT. 2🌟

Please join us on Sunday, May 17th as we give back to the extraordinary people that make us who we are - our managers, our bartenders, our waitresses, our chefs and kitchen staff, our barbacks, our bussers and our hostesses.

The first event, held on April 18th included 25+ restaurants and raised an estimated $100k in proceeds for our employees. The response from our communities was truly overwhelming!

All $$$ raised on this day will allow us to give back to our teams during this time of need.

A full list of participating restaurants will be coming soon!

#thegreatjerseyshoretakeout
#supportlocal #eatgood #jerseyshore - #regrann

Curious about the Mama Dove in the courtyard? Fret not! Mr. Gfroehrer and Mrs. Holter set up a live webcam so you can keep on eye on her!! Click the link on our website or visit dove.slheights.org. You may experience some offline moments, so please be patient, and refresh your viewing page. We've name her Love Dove in honor of what Mrs. Moloughney calls all her buddies!!

Love Dove will be pretty still most of the time now while she keeps her eggs safe, but stay tuned!!

Happy Earth Day @slheights!!! 🕊️🌎

post_text: Reposted from @wildandcrazycarnahans Don’t be fooled! While we do try to make the best of this scary time and #coronavirusquarantine and #distanceleaning...some days we are a hot mess. Today we have surpassed hot mess status. Our “classroom” is a mess, the students are melting down, and the teacher has little to no patience. Megan Doll is struggling too, as her peace sign on her shirt ripped. There’s even an ottoman under the kitchen table 🤷‍♀️. Thank you @slheights for your continued organization and support, as we need it today more than ever. #slheightsathome - #regrann
